## Purpose

```yaml
section: constitution.purpose
title: Purpose
status: active
owner: "{{ owner }}"
tags: [purpose, governance]
```

To provide a lightweight, zero-overhead structure with simple lists and a changelog to track objectives.

## Non-Negotiable Rules

```yaml
section: constitution.non-negotiable-rules
title: Non-Negotiable Rules
status: active
owner: "{{ owner }}"
tags: [rules, governance]
```

* Maintain a single `todo.md` for active tasks.
* Record user-facing updates in `CHANGELOG.md`.
* Changes to this constitution require owner approval.

## Task Status Scale

```yaml
section: constitution.task-statuses
title: Task Status Scale
status: active
owner: "{{ owner }}"
statuses:
  - open
  - in-progress
  - completed
tags: [status, tasks]
```

* **Open**: Pending action.
* **In Progress**: Work active.
* **Completed**: Verified and logged.

## Definition of Done

```yaml
section: constitution.definition-of-done
title: Definition of Done
status: active
owner: "{{ owner }}"
required_checks:
  - task_completed_in_todo
  - changelog_updated
  - test_verification_successful
tags: [dod, quality, validation]
```

To mark a task as completed:

1. Mark status as completed in `todo.md`.
2. Document user-facing changes in `CHANGELOG.md`.
3. Verify that tests pass.
